        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">1. Introduction</h2>

        <p>This document explains how to add or update your organisation&rsquo;s governance details on Get Information about Schools (GIAS).</p>

        <p>For more information about the national database of governors, the reasons for establishing it and the requirement to keep it up to date please see:</p>

        <p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/national-database-of-governors" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/national-database-of-governors (opens in new tab)</a></p>

        <p>for local authority-maintained schools: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/governance-in-maintained-schools">Maintained schools governance guide - Guidance - GOV.UK (www.gov.uk)</a></p>
        <p>for academies, free schools and academy trusts: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/-governance-in-academy-trusts">Academy trust governance guide - Guidance - GOV.UK (www.gov.uk)</a></p>

        <p>Please remember a term of office is one term elected for an individual in a specific governance role. If the individual is re-elected for another term this is a new record and the original record&rsquo;s term of office should not be extended.</p>

        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">2. Access to update your governance information</h2>
        <p>Governance information can only be updated by DfE Sign-in (DSI) account holders in schools, academies, multi-academy trusts (MATs) and secure single-academy trusts (SSATs). DSI accounts are managed locally by an approver within the organisation. It is both the establishment and group&rsquo;s responsibility to keep their governance information up to date. We are unable to provide access to local authorities and governance support service organisations to update establishment and groups&rsquo; governance details.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.1. Local authority-maintained schools</h3>
        <p>Sign in and go to your school record by using its name or unique reference number (URN). To edit governance details, select the governance tab, then &lsquo;Edit Governance&rsquo; and follow the steps in sections 4 and 5.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.2. Academies including free schools, university technology colleges (UTCs), city technology colleges (CTCs), studio schools and secure 16 to 19 academies</h3>
        <p>Sign in and go to your academy record by using its name or URN. To edit the governance details, select the governance tab, then &lsquo;Edit Governance&rsquo; and follow the steps in sections 4 and 5.</p>

        <p>For academies that are part of a multi-academy trust (MAT), governance information and your academy record can also be updated directly by the MAT (see 2.3 below).</p>

        <p>If your academy is part of a MAT and you do not have local governors, there is no requirement to add local governor details to your establishment record. In this case, please update the &lsquo;Establishment governance sharing&rsquo; option on your establishment record to <i>&lsquo;This academy is part of a multi-academy trust and does not have local governors&rsquo;</i>.</p>

        <p>Secure 16 to 19 academies do not have governance at the establishment level.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.3. Multi-academy trusts (MATs)</h3>
        <p>This <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qLVxLq-Jyqc" target="_blank">video (opens in new tab)</a> may help you when completing or updating your trust governance records.</p>

        <p>Sign in and go to your &lsquo;My trust&rsquo; page by using its name or reference number. This page gives details of your MAT and the academies and/or free schools within your MAT. You can edit both.</p>

        <p>From this page you can edit the governance details for your MAT by selecting the governance tab, then &lsquo;Edit Governance&rsquo; and follow the steps in section 4 of this guidance. You can also enter details of any shared governance (see section 4.7).</p>

        <p>Chair of trustee, trustee, member, accounting officer and chief financial officer details should only be added to the MAT record, there is no requirement to add them to the individual academy or free school records.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.3.1 Editing local governance details</h3>
        <p>To edit the local governance details for the academies in your MAT:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Select the tab &lsquo;Academies&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Go to the individual establishment</li>
            <li>Select the governance tab</li>
            <li>Select &lsquo;Edit Governance&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Follow the steps in section 4 of this guide</li>
        </ul>

        <p>If any of the academies in your MAT do not have local governors, then you will need to update the &lsquo;Establishment governance sharing&rsquo; option on the academy record to &lsquo;This academy is part of a multi-academy trust and does not have local governors&rsquo;.</p>

        <p>You can also suggest changes to details for your academies including headteacher details, address, telephone number, website and email address. Select &lsquo;Edit details&rsquo;, edit the required field and select &lsquo;Save&rsquo;.</p>

        <p>Most changes to academy records are sent for checking, please make sure any changes reflect your current funding agreement.</p>

        <p>Where a MAT operates a shared governance system, details should be included on the MAT record and will be available to be selected for each individual establishment as required.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">2.4 Secure single-academy trusts (SSATs)</h3>
        <p>After signing in to GIAS you can view the record for your SSAT. This page provides details about your SSAT and the secure 16 to 19 academy associated with it.</p>

        <p>From this page you can edit the governance details for your SSAT by selecting the governance tab, then &lsquo;Edit Governance&rsquo; and follow the steps in section 4 of this guide. You can also suggest changes to details for your academies including headteacher details, address, telephone number, website and email address. Select &lsquo;Edit details&rsquo;, edit the required field, click on &ldquo;Continue&rdquo;, check the proposed updates and click &ldquo;Accept and save&rdquo;.</p>

        <p>Most changes to secure 16 to 19 academy records are sent for checking, please make sure any changes reflect your current funding agreement.</p>

