        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">4. Add, edit or delete governance information via the governance tab</h2>
        <p>There are two methods to add or update governance data, either by directly entering information on the governance tab or using the bulk update method.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.1. Add new records via the governance tab</h3>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Select &lsquo;Edit governance&rsquo; from the governance tab</li>
            <li>
                <p>Select the role of the person you want to add, then select the &lsquo;Add&rsquo; button.</p>

                <p>For information: There can be only one:</p>

                <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                    <li>chair of governors</li>
                    <li>chair of trustees</li>
                    <li>chair of local governors</li>
                    <li>chair of shared local governors</li>
                    <li>accounting officer and</li>
                    <li>chief financial officer</li>
                </ul>

                <p>There can be multiple governors, local governors, shared local governors, members and trustees.</p>

                <p>There can only be one shared governance professional role, except on the multi-academy trust governance record where there can be more than one &ndash; shared governance professional &ndash; group.</p>
            </li>
            <li>Complete all the fields required to save the record then select &lsquo;Add&rsquo;.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.2. Update records via the governance tab</h3>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Select the governance tab and then &lsquo;Edit governance&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Select &lsquo;Edit&rsquo; below the role you want to edit; the record opens in edit mode</li>
            <li>Make the required changes. Complete all the fields required to save the record then select &lsquo;Save&rsquo;.</li>
        </ul>

        <p><b>For accounting officer and chief financial officer only:</b> the &lsquo;Date term of office ends&rsquo; is not editable. The date will be populated with the day before the date of appointment of the replacement chief financial officer/ accounting officer.</p>

        <p>If the term of office is extended for any governance role, please add this as a new appointment and do not change the end date for the historic record.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.3. Replace a fixed role via the governance tab</h3>
        <p>The following are classed as &lsquo;fixed&rsquo; roles:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>chair of governors</li>
            <li>chair of trustees</li>
            <li>chair of local governors</li>
            <li>chair of shared local governors</li>
            <li>accounting officer (AO)</li>
            <li>chief financial officer (CFO)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>When a chairs&rsquo; term of office ends, or the accounting office and chief financial officer leave their post their details on GIAS must be replaced with their replacement&rsquo;s details.</p>

        <p>To <b>replace</b> a &lsquo;fixed&rsquo; role:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Select the governance tab and select &lsquo;Edit&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Select &lsquo;Replace&rsquo; underneath the role you want to replace</li>
            <li>A new record opens in edit mode.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>There are a number of scenarios that need to be considered and depending on the options chosen, follow the instructions below:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list gias-list--alpha">
            <li>the chair needs to be replaced and <b>not reinstated</b> as a governor or trustee</li>
            <li>the chair needs to be replaced and <b>reinstated</b> as a governor or trustee</li>
            <li>the chair needs to be replaced by a <b>current</b> governor or trustee</li>
            <li>the chair needs to be replaced by a new governor or trustee</li>
        </ul>

        <p><b>Please note:</b> if the establishment has shared local governors the option of shared chair of local governors needs to be selected.</p>

        <p>Complete all the fields required to save the record then select &lsquo;Save&rsquo;. The original record for this role will be automatically archived when the save button is selected.</p>

        <p><b>For accounting officer and chief financial officer only:</b> the &lsquo;Date term of office ends&rsquo; is not editable. The date will be populated with the day before the date of appointment of the replacement chief financial officer/ accounting officer.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.4. Resignation or removal: editing and closing a record via the governance tab</h3>
        <p>When a governor, trustee, local governor, shared local governor, resigns, or is removed from, their post before the end of their term of office, or when a governance professional has resigned or is replaced, the &lsquo;Edit person&rsquo; option can be used to modify the term of office end date. This option can also be used for a SAT or MAT member who resigns, or is removed from, their member role.</p>

        <p>Once the update is made and the date is in the past the record will be moved to the &lsquo;Historic (left within last 12 months)&rsquo; section. This option also allows the details to be amended.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.5. Completed term of office: editing and deleting a record via the governance tab</h3>
        <p>The <b>&lsquo;Remove person&rsquo;</b> option should only be used:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>for those who have completed their term of office &ndash; selecting the, &lsquo;This person has completed their term of office&rsquo; option or</li>
            <li>to remove a record created in error &ndash; selecting the, &lsquo;Remove person&rsquo; option. A record that has been deleted (&lsquo;Remove person&rsquo;) cannot be recovered.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>There are two available options:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>
                <p><b>&lsquo;This person has completed their term&rsquo;.</b></p>
                <p>This should be used when a governor, trustee, member, local governor, shared local governor have <b>fully completed their term of office</b> or when a governance professional is replaced.</p>
                <p>Once this has been updated and the date is in the past the record will be moved to the &lsquo;Historic (left within last 12 months)&rsquo; section.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p><b>&lsquo;Remove person&rsquo;</b></p>
                <p>This option should only be used if the record was <b>created in error</b>. A record that has been deleted (&lsquo;Remove person&rsquo;) cannot be recovered.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.6. Delegated authority text box (multi-academy trusts (MATs) only)</h3>
        <p>Some MATs operate a governance model where it has delegated certain responsibilities to a single local committee (local governing body) or hub which may oversee 2 or more academies within the MAT. This is known as a &lsquo;shared governance&rsquo; model. The &lsquo;shared governance&rsquo; information needs to be completed before the individual academy governance information.</p>

        <p>In the governance tab, you can edit details of the delegated authority of the local governing body (LGB). Select &lsquo;Edit&rsquo; and use the text box to provide details of the level of delegated authority that an LGB has, including a shared LGB if applicable. Include in headline terms the role and remit of any LGBs and any governance functions delegated to them.</p>

        <p>Within a MAT with multiple shared local governance bodies, you should add a brief description of how their roles report to the MAT board.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.7. Create shared chair of local governing body, shared local governor and/or shared governance professional</h3>
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.7.1. MAT record</h3>
        <p>In the MAT governance tab under the &lsquo;Add person&rsquo; section, using the drop-down option list in &lsquo;select a role&rsquo; choose the type of shared governance role required and select &lsquo;Add person&rsquo;. Complete the record for that person and repeat for any other shared governance roles as required.</p>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.7.2. Individual academy record</h3>
        <p>To add the relevant shared chair of local governing body, shared local governor and shared governance professional (if required) to the relevant academy select the academy record:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Go into the governance tab</li>
            <li>Under governor sharing select &lsquo;Edit governor sharing&rsquo;</li>
            <li>Select the &lsquo;This establishment has local governors and also shares governors with other academies in the trust.&rsquo; option and then select &lsquo;Save governor sharing&rsquo;</li>
        </ul>

        <p>To add the relevant shared chair of local governing body, shared local governor and/or shared governance professional into the academy record go to the &lsquo;Add person&rsquo; section:</p>

        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
            <li>Using the drop-down option list in &lsquo;select a role&rsquo; choose the shared chair of local governing body &ndash; establishment, shared local governor - establishment or shared governance professional - establishment.</li>
            <li>Select &lsquo;Add person&rsquo;. From the list that appears select either &lsquo;shared chair of local governing body - establishment&rsquo;, &lsquo;shared local governor -establishment&rsquo; or shared governance professional - establishment.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">4.8 Secure single-academy trust (SSAT)</h3>
        <p>Original signatory member, we require information if a member (organisation or individual) was one of the original signatory member(s)</p>

        <p>Original chair of trustees, we require information if the chair of trustees was the original chair of trustees</p>

        <p>A SSAT can have both:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
            <li>
                <p><b>Member &ndash; organisation:</b> a SSAT can have one or more member &ndash; organisations. The original and/or subsequent members of an academy trust assure themselves that the governance of the trust is effective and that trustees are acting in accordance with the trust&rsquo;s charitable objects. Members&rsquo; powers are set out in the trust&rsquo;s articles of association and in the <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/46/section/168">Companies Act 2006</a></p>
                <p><b>Member &ndash; individual:</b> a SSAT can have one or more member &ndash; individuals. An individual person(s) appointed into the member role (not a trustee). The original and/or subsequent members of an academy trust assure themselves that the governance of the trust is effective and that trustees are acting in accordance with the trust&rsquo;s charitable objects. Members&rsquo; powers are set out in the trust&rsquo;s articles of association and in the <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2006/46/section/168">Companies Act 2006</a></p>
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>Appointed by:</p>
